raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Experience for Education: For every year of full-time specific field experience, the person shall be credited with one year of degree qualifications toward the values stated in the labor category descriptions. Two years will equal an associate's degree, 4 years will equal a bachelor's degree, 6 years will equal a master's degree and 8 years will equal a doctorate degree.  Education for Experience: An associate's degree will equal 2 years of experience. A bachelor’s degree will equal 4 years of experience. A master’s degree will equal 6 years of experience. A doctorate degree will equal 8 years of experience.
